Moody’s Aug. U.S. Credit Card Indexes: Summary

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-09-23T14:56:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/moody-s-aug-u-s-credit-card-indexes-summary-table-.html
The amount of bad U.S.  credit
card  loans written off as uncollectible fell to 6.02 percent
at an annualized rate in Aug., according to Moody’s.  The amount of loan balances in which a monthly payment
was 30 days or more past due fell to 3.04 percent annualized
from 4.7 percent in the same month last year.  The Credit Card Index report is based on the credit
performance data for approximately 255 individual credit
card backed securities rated by Moody’s.  The index sample
includes more than $445 billion of bank credit card
receivables that have been outstanding for at least a year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Tanzi in Washington at   atanzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  